    <ImplicitInverseRef name="cmbTblColFilter" id="06731533-701d-40ab-8ff1-453ed35be2a9">
        <embedded/>
        <type name="CMUI_ComboBox"/>
        <text>

		** To make use of column data filtering on a "Table" that
		does NOT use column Organiser, call "row2FilterSetup" on the table,
		make sure the table has a fixed Row (Heading row), and just one.
		
		If the method is called with the Boolean set to true, a new Row 2 will be added
		that contains a cloned combo box to filter by, and the combos will be populated.
		Call it with 'false' to just re-populate the values in the combos.
		
		Four "row2Filter" methods on "Table" do all the work, but rely on this specific
		comboBox on "CM_BaseForm" and its associated click method.
		
		&lt;Table&gt;.row2FilterSetup( self.cmbTblColFilter, true );</text>
    </ImplicitInverseRef>
